Load three separate CSV files into Python
Inspect each file to diagnose its problems
Build a pipeline that cleans each file and combines them into one master dataset
Produce the first descriptive statistics to understand the overall distribution
Nothing about this process is optional. A flawed data-loading step corrupts every subsequent result. A data scientist who skips the inspection ritual discovers the corruption only at the end — after hours of work. This lesson makes you rigorous from the start.

